(CNN) – A 911 dispatcher has been fired after being accused of mishandling a call during the recent mass shooting at a grocery store in Buffalo, New York.

Latisha Rogers, an assistant office manager at the Tops supermarket where a gunman opened fire last month, said she dropped to the ground after hearing the shots and called 911, whispering out of fear the shooter might hear her.

Officials say they teach 911 dispatchers that if someone is whispering, it probably means they’re in trouble, but Rogers said the Buffalo dispatcher responded: “I can’t hear you. Why are you whispering? You don’t have to whisper. They can’t hear you.”

Shortly after that, Rogers said the dispatcher hung up the phone.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/AUNGDQV</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Copperbrat]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>More like corporate greed!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/XitFtB0</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8A0q1Zo.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XitFtB0</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Futroman]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Catfished</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/3KLeJus</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/92P5NbP.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/3KLeJus</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[AsshatTheCat]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Another time</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/xT75QoU</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eZbBETC.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/xT75QoU</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DaiMudda]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Almost forgot about this gem.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/6p4wBFT</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZoQLOyh.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Seems relevant considering current events.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/6p4wBFT</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[PastorBeckyAKAEvilLlLlama]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Let me slide your cheeks apart and gently insert my soup</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/NUpzKV2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nlqi8oG.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Good ol Buffalo Chicken Chowder.  A hearty, slightly spicy bowl of silky comfort</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/spYDQYr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Ok, before anyone asks...

Start by making a gorgonzola cream sauce.  Reduce some heavy whip by 1/4 and add enough gorg to make it good and skunky (that'll even out later).  Pinch of pepper and set aside.
Saute onion, celery, carrot and red pepper.  Add garlic.  Add chicken or veggie broth.  Add some diced Yukon gold potatoes and boil until fork tender.  Add the chicken I forgot to mention I diced, seasoned, and seared earlier.  Add the gorg sauce to the broth and veg, then add enough roux to thicken it to your liking.  The best part comes when you add a shitload of your favorite hot sauce... Frank's works great but get crazy with it.  Top with a little diced celery for crunch and some more gorg to give it that hot wing experience.  This one is a banger, guys.

Most Viral edit - you guys did it again!  Man, y'all make me feel awful nice.  Thanks for the comments and awards and updoots!  Stay fresh, cheese bags!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/NUpzKV2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[linecookdaddy]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Gimme your plants!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/p1DDW5P</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JOXEVwG.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Snippity-snip, no house plant is safe!

